In ontology and the philosophy of mind, a 'non-physical entitiy' is a spirit or
being that exists outside of normal reality. Their existence divides the
philosophical schools of physicalism and dualism, with the latter holding that
they do and the former that they do not. If one posits that non-physical
entities can exist, there exist further debates as to their inherent natures and
their position relative to physical entities.
